obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29913)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29913&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hindu Succession Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29914)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29914&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act applies--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person, who is a Hindu by religion in any of its forms or developments, including a`
  line `Virashaiva, a Lingayat or a follower of the Brahmo, Prarthana or Arya Samaj,`
  line
  line `(b) to any person who is a Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh by religion, and`
  line
  line `(c) to any other person who is not a Muslim, Christian, Parsi or Jew by religion, unless it is`
  line `proved that any such person would not have been governed by the Hindu law or by any custom or`
  line `usage as part of that law in respect of any of the matters dealt with herein if this Act had not been`
  line passed.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The following persons are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or Sikhs by religion, as the case`
  line `may be:--`
  line
  line `(a) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, both of whose parents are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or`
  line `Sikhs by religion;`
  line
  line `(b) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, one of whose parents is a Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh`
  line `by religion and who is brought up as a member of the tribe, community, group or family to which`
  line `such parent belongs or belonged;`
  line
  line `(c) any person who is a convert or reconvert to the Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh religion.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), nothing contained in this Act shall apply`
  line `to the members of any Scheduled Tribe within the meaning of clause (25) of article 366 of the`
  line `Constitution unless the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(3) The expression "Hindu" in any portion of this Act shall be construed as if it included a person`
  line `who, though not a Hindu by religion, is, nevertheless, a person to whom this Act applies by virtue of the`
  line `provisions contained in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29915)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29915&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "agnate" person is said to be an agnate of another if the two are related by blood or`
  line `adoption wholly through males;`
  line
  line `(b) "aliyasantana law" means the system of law applicable to persons who, if this Act had not`
  line `been passed, would have been governed by the Madras Aliyasantana Act, 1949, (Madras Act 9 of`
  line `1949) or by the customary aliyasantana law with respect to the matters for which provision is made in`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cognate" person is said to be a cognate of another if the two are related by blood or`
  line `adoption but not wholly through males;`
  line
  line `(d) the expressions "custom" and "usage" signify any rule which, having been continuously and`
  line `uniformly observed for a long time, has obtained the force of law among Hindus in any local area,`
  line `tribe, community, group or family:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rule is certain and not unreasonable or opposed to public policy: and`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a rule applicable only to a family it has not been discontinued`
  line `by the family;`
  line
  line `(e) full blood "half blood" and "uterine blood"--`
  line
  line `(i) two persons are said to be related to each other by full blood when they are descended`
  line `from a common ancestor by the same wife, and by half blood when they are descended from a`
  line `common ancestor but by different wives;`
  line
  line `(ii) two persons are said to be related to each other by uterine blood when they are descended`
  line `from a common ancestress but by different husbands;`
  line
  line `Explanation.In this clause ancestor includes the father and ancestress the mother;`
  line
  line `(f) "heir" means any person, male or female, who is entitled to succeed to the property of an`
  line `intestate under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "intestate"a person is deemed to die intestate in respect of property of which he or she has`
  line `not made a testamentary disposition capable of taking effect;`
  line
  line `(h) "marumakkattayam law" means the system of law applicable to persons`
  line
  line `(a) who, if this Act had not been passed, would have been governed by the Madras`
  line `Marumakkattayam Act, 1932 (Madras Act 22 of 1933); the Travancore Nayar Act (2 of 1100K);`
  line
  line `the Travancore Ezhava Act (3 of 1100K); the Travancore Nanjinad Vellala Act (6 of 1101K); the`
  line `Travancore Kshatriya Act (7 of 1108K); the Travancore Krishnanvaka Marumakkathayee (Act 7`
  line `of 1115K); the Cochin Marumakkathayam Act (33 of 1113K); or the Cochin Nayar Act (29 of`
  line `1113K); with respect to the matters for which provision is made in this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) who belong to any community, the members of which are largely domiciled in the State of`
  line `Travancore Cochin or Madras ^2[as it existed immediately before the 1st November, 1956], and`
  line `who, if this Act had not been passed, would have been governed with respect to the matters for`
  line `which provision is made in this Act by any system of inheritance in which descent is traced`
  line `through the female line;`
  line
  line `but does not include the aliyasantana law;`
  line
  line `(i) "nambudri law" means the system of law applicable to persons who, if this Act had not been`
  line `passed, would have been governed by the Madras Nambudri Act, 1932 Madras Act (21 of 1933); the`
  line `Cochin Nambudri Act (17 of 111K); or the Travancore Malayala Brahmin Act (3 of 1106K); with`
  line `respect to the matters for which provision is made in this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "related" means related by legitimate kinship:`
  line
  line `Provided that illegitimate children shall be deemed to be related to their mother and to one`
  line `another, and their legitimate descendants shall be deemed to be related to them and to one another;`
  line
  line `and any word expressing relationship or denoting a relative shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, words importing the masculine gender shall not`
  line `be taken to include females.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29916)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Overriding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by Act 39 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-9-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29916&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) any text, rule or interpretation of Hindu law or any custom or usage as part of that law in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to have effect with respect to any`
  line `matter for which provision is made in this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any other law in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to apply`
  line `to Hindus in so far as it is inconsistent with any of the provisions contained in this Act.`
  line
  line ^1*****
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29917)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Act not to apply to certain properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29917&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall not apply to―`
  line
  line `(i) any property succession to which is regulated by the Indian Succession Act, 1925 ( 39 of`
  line `1925), by reason of the provisions contained in section 21 of the Special Marriage Act, 1954 (43 of`
  line `1954);`
  line
  line `(ii) any estate which descends to a single heir by the terms of any covenant or agreement entered`
  line `into by the Ruler of any Indian State with the Government of India or by the terms of any enactment`
  line `passed before the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Valiamma Thampuran Kovilagam Estate and the Palace Fund administered by the Palace`
  line `Administration Board by reason of the powers conferred by Proclamation (IX of 1124) dated 29th`
  line `June, 1949, promulgated by the Maharaja of Cochin.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29918)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Devolution of interest in coparcenary property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 9-9-2005)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29918&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) On and from the commencement of the`
  line `Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005 (39 of 2005), in a Joint Hindu family governed by the`
  line `Mitakshara law, the daughter of a coparcener shall,`
  line
  line `(a) by birth become a coparcener in her own right the same manner as the son;`
  line
  line `(b) have the same rights in the coparcenery property as she would have had if she had been a son;`
  line
  line `(c) be subject to the same liabilities in respect of the said coparcenery property as that of a son,`
  line `and any reference to a Hindu Mitakshara coparcener shall be deemed to include a reference to a daughter`
  line `of a coparcener:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect or invalidate any disposition or`
  line `alienation including any partition or testamentary disposition of property which had taken place before the`
  line `20th day of December, 2004.`
  line
  line `(2) Any property to which a female Hindu becomes entitled by virtue of sub-section (1) shall be held`
  line `by her with the incidents of coparcenary ownership and shall be regarded, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, as property capable of being disposed of`
  line `by her by testamentary disposition.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a Hindu dies after the commencement of the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005`
  line `(39 of 2005), his interest in the property of a Joint Hindu family governed by the Mitakshara law, shall`
  line `devolve by testamentary or intestate succession, as the case may be, under this Act and not by`
  line `survivorship, and the coparcenery property shall be deemed to have been divided as if a partition had`
  line `taken place and,`
  line
  line `(a) the daughter is allotted the same share as is allotted to a son;`
  line
  line `(b) the share of the pre-deceased son or a pre-deceased daughter, as they would have got had they`
  line `been alive at the time of partition, shall be allotted to the surviving child of such pre-deceased son or`
  line `of such pre-deceased daughter; and`
  line
  line `(c) the share of the pre-deceased child of a pre-deceased son or of a pre-deceased daughter, as`
  line `such child would have got had he or she been alive at the time of the partition, shall be allotted to the`
  line `child of such pre-deceased child of the pre-deceased son or a pre-deceased daughter, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the interest of a Hindu Mitakshara coparcener`
  line `shall be deemed to be the share in the property that would have been allotted to him if a partition of the`
  line `property had taken place immediately before his death, irrespective of whether he was entitled to claim`
  line `partition or not.`
  line
  line `(4) After the commencement of the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005 (39 of 2005), no court`
  line `shall recognise any right to proceed against a son, grandson or great-grandson for the recovery of any debt`
  line `due from his father, grandfather or great-grandfather solely on the ground of the pious obligation under`
  line `the Hindu law, of such son, grandson or great-grandson to discharge any such debt:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any debt contracted before the commencement of the Hindu Succession`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2005 (39 of 2005), nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect`
  line
  line `(a) the right of any creditor to proceed against the son, grandson or great-grandson, as the case`
  line `may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) any alienation made in respect of or in satisfaction of, any such debt, and any such right or`
  line `alienation shall be enforceable under the rule of pious obligation in the same manner and to the same`
  line `extent as it would have been enforceable as if the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005`
  line `(39 of 2005) had not been enacted.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of clause (a), the expression son, grandson or great-grandson`
  line `shall be deemed to refer to the son, grandson or great-grandson, as the case may be, who was born or`
  line `adopted prior to the commencement of the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005 (39 of 2005).`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to a partition, which has been effected before the`
  line `20th day of December, 2004`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section partition means any partition made by execution of`
  line `a deed of partition duly registered under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) or partition effected by a`
  line `decree of a court.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections in Central Act 30 of 1956.--In the Hindu Succession Act, 1956 (Central`
  line `Act 30 of 1956) after section 6, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `[6A. Equal rights to daughter in co-parcenary property.Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 6 of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a joint Hindu family governed by Mitakshara law, the daughter of a co-parcener shall by`
  line `birth become a co-parcener in her own right in the same manner as the son and have the same rights`
  line `in the co-parcenary property as she would have had if she had been a son inclusive of the right to`
  line `claim by survivorship and shall be subject to the same liabilities and disabilities in respect thereto as`
  line `the son;`
  line
  line `(b) at a partition in such Joint Hindu Family the co-parcenary property shall be so divided as to`
  line `allot to a daughter the same share as is allotable to a son:`
  line
  line `Provided that the share which a predeceased son or a predeceased daughter would have got at the`
  line `partition if he or she had been alive at the time of the partition, shall be allotted to the surviving child`
  line `of such predeceased son or of such predeceased daughter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the share allotable to the predeceased child of the predeceased son or of a`
  line `predeceased daughter, if such child had been alive at the time of the partition, shall be allotted to the`
  line `child of such predeceased child of the predeceased son or of such predeceased daughter, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(c) any property to which a female Hindu becomes entitled by virtue of the provisions of clause`
  line `(a) shall be held by her with the incidents of co-parcenary ownership and shall be regarded,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, as`
  line `property capable of being disposed of by her by will or other testamentary disposition;`
  line
  line `(d) nothing in clause (b) shall apply to a daughter married prior to or to a partition which had`
  line `been effected before the commencement of Hindu Succession (Karnataka Amendment) Act, 1990.`
  line
  line `6B. Interest to devolve by survivorship on death.--When a female Hindu dies after the`
  line `commencement of the Hindu Succession (Karnataka Amendment) Act, 1990, having at the time of her`
  line `death an interest in a Mitakshara co-parcenary property, her interest in the property shall devolve by`
  line `survivorship upon the surviving members of the co-parcenary and not in accordance with this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the deceased had left any child or child of a pre-deceased child, the interest of the`
  line `deceased in the Mitakshara co-parcenary property shall devolve by testamentary or intestate succession,`
  line `as the case may be, under this Act and not by survivorship.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--(1) For the purposes of this section the interest of female Hindu Mitakshara coparcener shall be deemed to be the share in the property that would have been allotted to her if a partition`
  line `of the property had taken place immediately before her death, irrespective of whether she was entitled to`
  line `claim partition or not.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in the proviso to this section shall be construed as enabling a person who,`
  line `before the death of the deceased had separated himself or herself from the co-parcenary, or any of his or`
  line `her heirs to claim on intestacy a share in the interest referred to therein.`
  line
  line `6C. Preferential right to acquire property in certain cases.--(1) Where, after the commencement`
  line `of Hindu Succession (Karnataka Amendment) Act, 1990 an interest in any immovable property of an`
  line `intestate or in any business carried on by him or her, whether solely or in conjunction with others`
  line `devolves under sections 6A or 6B upon two or more heirs and any one of such heirs proposes to transfer`
  line `his or her interest in the property or business, the other heirs shall have a preferential right to acquire the`
  line `interest proposed to be transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The consideration for which any interest in the property of the deceased may be transferred under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, in the absence of any agreement between the parties, be determined by the court, on`
  line `application, being made to it in this behalf, and if any person proposing to acquire the interest is not`
  line `willing to acquire it for the consideration so determined, such person shall be liable to pay all costs of or`
  line `incidental to the application.`
  line
  line `(3) If there are two or more heirs proposing to acquire any interest under, this section, that heir who`
  line `offers the highest consideration for the transfer shall be preferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section 'Court' means the court within the limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `immoveable property is situate or the business is carried on, and includes any other court which the State`
  line `Government may by notification in the official Gazette specify in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `[vide Karnataka Act 23 of 1994, sec. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (29919)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Devolution of interest in the property of a tarwad, tavazhi, kutumba, kavaru or illom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29919&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Hindu to whom the marumakkattayam or nambudri law would have applied if this`
  line `Act had not been passed dies after the commencement of this Act, having at the time of his or her death`
  line `an interest in the property of a tarwad, tavazhi or illom, as the case may be, his or her interest in the`
  line `property shall devolve by testamentary or intestate succession, as the case may be, under this Act and not`
  line `according to the marumakkattayam or nambudri law.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this sub-section, the interest of a Hindu in the property of a`
  line `tarwad, tavazhi or illom shall be deemed to be the share in the property of the tarwad, tavazhi or illom, as`
  line `the case may be, that would have fallen to him or her if a partition of that property per capita had been`
  line `made immediately before his or her death among all the members of the tarwad, tavazhi or illom, as the`
  line `case may be, then living, whether he or she was entitled to claim such partition or not under the`
  line `marumakkattayam or nambudri law applicable to him or her, and such share shall be deemed to have been`
  line `allotted to him or her absolutely.`
  line
  line `(2) When a Hindu to whom the aliyasantana law would have applied if this Act had not been passed`
  line `dies after the commencement of this Act, having at the time of his or her death an undivided interest in`
  line `the property of a kutumba or kavaru, as the case may be, his or her interest in the property shall devolve`
  line `by testamentary or intestate succession, as the case may be, under this Act and not according to the`
  line `aliyasantana law.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this sub-section, the interest of a Hindu in the property of a kutumba or kavaru shall be deemed to be the share in the property of the kutumba or kavaru, as the case`
  line `may be, that would have fallen to him or her if a partition of that property per capita had been made`
  line `immediately before his or her death among all the members of the kutumba or kavaru, as the case may be,`
  line `then living, whether he or she was entitled to claim such partition or not under the aliyasantana law, and`
  line `such share shall be deemed to have been allotted to him or her absolutely.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), when a sthanamdar dies after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the sthanam property held by him shall devolve upon the members of the`
  line `family to which the sthanamdar belonged and the heirs of the sthanamdar as if the sthanam property had`
  line `been divided per capita immediately before the death of the sthanamdar among himself and all the`
  line `members of his family then living,, and the shares falling to the members of his family and the heirs of the`
  line `sthanamdar shall be held by them as their separate property.`
  line
  line `ExplanationFor the purposes of this sub-section, the family of a sthanamdar shall include every`
  line `branch of that family, whether divided or undivided, the male members of which would have been`
  line `entitled by any custom or usage to succeed to the position of sthanamdar if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (29920)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `General rules of succession in the case of males.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29920&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The property of a male Hindu dying intestate`
  line `shall devolve according to the provisions of this Chapter:--`
  line
  line `(a) firstly, upon the heirs, being the relatives specified in class I of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) secondly, if there is no heir of class I, then upon the heirs, being the relatives specified in class`
  line `II of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(c) thirdly, if there is no heir of any of the two classes, then upon the agnates of the deceased; and`
  line
  line `(d) lastly, if there is no agnate, then upon the cognates of the deceased.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (29921)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Order of succession among heirs in the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29921&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Among the heirs specified in the Schedule,`
  line `those in class I shall take simultaneously and to the exclusion of all other heirs; those in the first entry in`
  line `class II shall be preferred to those in the second entry; those in the second entry shall be preferred to those`
  line `in the third entry; and so on in succession.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (29922)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Distribution of property among heirs in class I of the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29922&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The property of an intestate`
  line `shall be divided among the heirs in class I of the Schedule in accordance with the following rules:―`
  line
  line `Rule 1.―The intestates widow, or if there are more widows than one, all the widows together,`
  line `shall take one share.`
  line
  line `Rule 2.―The surviving sons and daughters and the mother of the intestate shall each take one`
  line share.
  line
  line `Rule 3.―The heirs in the branch of each pre-deceased son or each pre-deceased daughter of the`
  line `intestate shall take between them one share.`
  line
  line `Rule 4.―The distribution of the share referred to in Rule 3`
  line
  line `(i) among the heirs in the branch of the pre-deceased son shall be so made that his widow (or`
  line `widows together) and the surviving sons and daughters get equal portions; and the branch of his`
  line `pre-deceased sons gets the same portion;`
  line
  line `(ii) among the heirs in the branch of the pre-deceased daughter shall be so made that the`
  line `surviving sons and daughters get equal portions.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (29923)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Distribution of property among heirs in class II of the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29923&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The property of an intestate`
  line `shall be divided between the heirs specified in any one entry in class II of the Schedule so that they, share`
  line equally.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (29924)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Order of succession among agnates and congnates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29924&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The order of succession among agnates or`
  line `cognates, as the case may be, shall be determined in accordance with the rules of preference laid down`
  line `hereunder:`
  line
  line `Rule 1.—Of two heirs, the one who has fewer or no degrees of ascent is preferred.`
  line
  line `Rule 2.—Where the number of degrees of ascent is the same or none, that heir is preferred who`
  line `has fewer or no degrees of descent.`
  line
  line `Rule 3.—Where neither heir is entitled to be preferred to the other under Rule 1 or Rule 2 they`
  line `take simultaneously.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (29925)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Computation of degrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29925&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of determining the order of succession among`
  line `agnates or cognates, relationship shall be reckoned from the intestate to the heir in terms of degrees of`
  line `ascent or degrees of descent or both, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Degrees of ascent and degrees of descent shall be computed inclusive of the intestate.`
  line
  line `(3) Every generation constitutes a degree either ascending or descending.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (29926)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Property of a female Hindu to be her absolute property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29926&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any property possessed by a`
  line `female Hindu, whether acquired before or after the commencement of this Act, shall be held by her as full`
  line `owner thereof and not as a limited owner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this sub-section, "property" includes both movable and immovable property`
  line `acquired by a female Hindu by inheritance or devise, or at a partition, or in lieu of maintenance or arrears`
  line `of maintenance, or by gift from any person, whether a relative or not, before, at or after her marriage, or`
  line `by her own skill or exertion, or by purchase or by prescription, or in any other manner whatsoever, and`
  line `also any such property held by her as stridhana immediately before the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to any property acquired by way of gift or under`
  line `a will or any other instrument or under a decree or order of a civil court or under an award where the`
  line `terms of the gift, will or other instrument or the decree, order or award prescribe a restricted estate in such`
  line property.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (29927)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `General rules of succession in the case of female Hindus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29927&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The property of a female Hindu`
  line `dying intestate shall devolve according to the rules set out in section 16,`
  line
  line `(a) firstly, upon the sons and daughters (including the children of any pre-deceased son or`
  line `daughter) and the husband;`
  line
  line `(b) secondly, upon the heirs of the husband;`
  line
  line `(c) thirdly, upon the mother and father;`
  line
  line `(d) fourthly, upon the heirs of the father; and`
  line
  line `(e) lastly, upon the heirs of the mother.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),`
  line
  line `(a) any property inherited by a female Hindu from her father or mother shall devolve, in the`
  line `absence of any son or daughter of the deceased (including the children of any pre-deceased son or`
  line `daughter) not upon the other heirs referred in sub-section (1) in the order specified therein, but upon`
  line `the heirs of the father; and`
  line
  line `(b) any property inherited by a female Hindu from her husband or from her father-in-law shall`
  line `devolve, in the absence of any son or daughter of the deceased (including the children of any`
  line `pre-deceased son or daughter) not upon the other heirs referred to in sub-section (1) in the order`
  line `specified therein, but upon the heirs of the husband.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Kerala.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 15.--In the Hindu Succession Act, 1956 (Central Act 30 of 1956), in section`
  line `15, after clause (b) of sub-section (2), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(c)" any property inherited by a female Hindu from her pre-deceased son shall devolve, not upon the`
  line `other heirs referred to in sub-section (1) in the order specified therein, but upon the heirs of the predeceased son from whom she inherited the property."`
  line
  line `[vide Kerala Act 17 of 2016, sec. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (29928)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Order of succession and manner of distribution among heirs of a female Hindu.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29928&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The order`
  line `of succession among the heirs referred to in section 15 shall be, and the distribution of the intestate's`
  line `property among those heirs shall take place according to the following rules, namely:―`
  line
  line `Rule 1.―Among the heirs specified in sub-section (1) of section 15, those in one entry shall be`
  line `preferred to those in any succeeding entry, and those included in the same entry shall take simultaneously.`
  line
  line `Rule 2.―If any son or daughter of the intestate had pre-deceased the intestate leaving his or her own`
  line `children alive at the time of the intestates death, the children of such son or daughter shall take between`
  line `them the share which such son or daughter would have taken if living at the intestates death.`
  line
  line `Rule 3.―The devolution of the property of the intestate on the heirs referred to in clauses (b), (d) and`
  line `(e) of sub-section (1) and in sub-section (2) of section 15 shall be in the same order and according to the`
  line `same rules as would have applied if the property had been the father's or the mother's or the husband's as the case may be, and such person had died intestate in respect thereof immediately after the intestate's`
  line death.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (29929)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Special provisions respecting persons governed by marumakkattayam and aliyasantana laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29929&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 8, 10, 15 and 23 shall have effect in relation to persons who would`
  line `have been governed by the marumakkattayam law or aliyasantana law if this Act had not been passed as if`
  line
  line `(i) for sub-clauses (c) and (d) of section 8, the following had been substituted, namely:`
  line
  line `"(c) thirdly, if there is no heir of any of the two classes, then upon his relatives, whether agnates or cognates.";`
  line
  line `(ii) for clauses (a) to (e) of sub-section (1) of section 15, the following had been substituted,`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `"(a) firstly, upon the sons and daughters (including the children of any pre-deceased son or`
  line `daughter) and the mother;`
  line
  line `(b) secondly, upon the father and the husband;`
  line
  line `(c) thirdly, upon the heirs of the mother;`
  line
  line `(d) fourthly, upon the heirs of the father; and`
  line
  line `(e) lastly, upon the heirs of the husband.";`
  line
  line `(iii) clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 15 had been omitted;`
  line
  line `(iv) section 23 had been omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (29930)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Full blood preferred to half blood.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29930&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Heirs related to an intestate by full blood shall be preferred`
  line `to heirs related by half blood, if the nature of the relationship is the same in every other respect.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (29931)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mode of succession of two or more heirs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29931&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If two or more heirs succeed together to the property`
  line `of an intestate, they shall take the property,―`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, per capita and not per stirpes; and`
  line
  line `(b) as tenants-in-common and not as joint tenants.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (29932)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right of child in womb.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29932&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `A child who was in the womb at the time of the death of an intestate`
  line `and who is subsequently born alive shall have the same right to inherit to the intestate as if he or she had`
  line `been born before the death of the intestate, and the inheritance shall be deemed to vest in such a case with`
  line `effect from the date of the death of the intestate.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (29933)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Presumption in cases of simultaneous deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29933&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where two persons have died in circumstances`
  line `rendering it uncertain whether either of them, and if so which, survived the other, then, for all purposes`
  line `affecting succession to property, it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, that the younger`
  line `survived the elder.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (29934)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Preferential right to acquire property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29934&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, an interest in any immovable property of an intestate, or in any business carried on by him or`
  line `her, whether solely or in conjunction with others, devolves upon two or more heirs specified in class I of`
  line `the Schedule, and any one of such heirs proposes to transfer his or her interest in the property or business,`
  line `the other heirs shall have a preferential right to acquire the interest proposed to be transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The consideration for which any interest in the property of the deceased may be transferred under`
  line `this section shall, in the absence of any agreement between the parties, be determined by the court on`
  line `application being made to it in this behalf, and if any person proposing to acquire the interest is not`
  line `willing to acquire it for the consideration so determined, such person shall be liable to pay all costs of or`
  line `incident to the application.`
  line
  line `(3) If there are two or more heirs specified in class I of the Schedule proposing to acquire any interest`
  line `under this section, that heir who offers the highest consideration for the transfer shall be preferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation.―In this section, "court" means the court within the limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `immovable property is situate or the business is carried on, and includes any other court which the State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (29935)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Omitted.
  content `[Special provision respecting dwelling-houses.]Omitted by the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005 (39 of 2005), s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-9-2005).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29935&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (29942)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29942&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `[Certain windows re-marrying may not inherit as windows.] ---Omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-9-`
  line `2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (29943)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Murderer disqualified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29943&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A person who commits murder or abets the commission of murder`
  line `shall be disqualified from inheriting the property of the person murdered, or any other property in`
  line `furtherance of the succession to which he or she committed or abetted the commission of the murder.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (29944)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Convert’s descendants disqualified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29944&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where, before or after the commencement of this Act, a`
  line `Hindu has ceased or ceases to be a Hindu by conversion to another religion, children born to him or her`
  line `after such conversion and their descendants shall be disqualified from inheriting the property of any of`
  line `their Hindu relatives, unless such children or descendants are Hindus at the time when the succession`
  line opens.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (29945)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Succession when heir disqualified`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29945&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If any person is disqualified from inheriting any property`
  line `under this Act, it shall devolve as if such person had died before the intestate.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (29946)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Disease, defect, etc., not to disqualify`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29946&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be disqualified from succeeding to any`
  line `property on the ground of any disease, defect or deformity, or save as provided in this Act, on any other`
  line `ground whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (29947)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Failure of heirs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29947&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If an intestate has left no heir qualified to succeed to his or her property in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, such property shall devolve on the Government; and the`
  line `Government shall take the property subject to all the obligations and liabilities to which an heir would`
  line `have been subject.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Tamil Nadu`
  line
  line `In the Hindu Succession Act, 1956 (hereinafter referred to as the principal act), after chapter II, the`
  line `following chapter shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"CHAPTER II-A,`
  line
  line `Succession by survivorship.`
  line
  line `29-A. Equal rights to daughter in coparcenary property.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 6 of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a Joint Hindu Family governed by Mitakshara Law, the daughter of a coparcener shall`
  line `by birth become a coparcener in her own right in the same manner as a son and have the same`
  line `rights in the coparcenary property as she would have had if she had been a son, inclusive of the`
  line `right to claim by survivorship; and shall be subject to the same liabilities and disabilities in`
  line `respect thereto as the son;`
  line
  line `(ii) at a partition in such a Joint Hindu Family the coparcenary property shall be so divided as`
  line `to allot to a daughter the same share as is allotable to a son:`
  line
  line `Provided that the share which a pre-deceased son or a pre-deceased daughter would have got`
  line `at the partition if he or she had been alive at the time of the partition shall be allotted to the`
  line `surviving child of such pre-deceased son or of such pre-deceased daughter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the share allotable to the pre-deceased child of a predeceased son or of a`
  line `pre-deceased daughter, if such child had been alive at the time of the partition, shall be allotted to`
  line `the child of such pre-deceased child of the predeceased son or of the pre-deceased daughter, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(iii) any property to which a female Hindu becomes entitled by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `clause (i) shall be held by her with the incidents of coparcenary ownership and shall be regarded,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, as`
  line `property capable of being disposed of by her by will or other testamentary disposition;`
  line
  line `(iv) nothing in this Chapter shall apply to a daughter married before the date of the`
  line `commencement of the Hindu Succession (Tamil Nadu Amendment) Act, 1989;`
  line
  line `(v) nothing in clause (ii) shall apply to a partition which had been effected before the date of`
  line `the commencement of the Hindu Succession (Tamil Nadu Amendment) Act, 1989.`
  line
  line `29-B. Interest to devolve by survivorship on death.--When a female Hindu dies after the date`
  line `of the commencement of the Hindu Succession (Tamil Nadu Amendment) Act, 1989, having, at the`
  line `time of her death, an interest in a Mitakshara coparcenary property by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `section 29-A, her interest in the property shall devolve by survivorship upon the surviving members`
  line `of the coparcenary and not in accordance with this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the deceased had left any child or child of a pre-deceased child, the interest of the`
  line `deceased in the Mitakshara coparcenary property shall devolve by testamentary or intestate`
  line `succession, as the case may be, under this Act and not by survivorship.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this section, the interest of a female Hindu Mitakshara`
  line `coparcener shall be deemed to be the share in the property that would have been allotted to her if a`
  line `partition of the property had taken place immediately before her death, irrespective of whether she`
  line `was entitled to claim partition or not.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--Nothing contained in the proviso to this section shall be construed as enabling a`
  line `person who, before the death of the deceased, had separated himself or herself from the coparcenary`
  line `or any of his or her heirs to claim on intestacy a share in the interest referred to therein.`
  line
  line `29-C. Preferential right to acquire property in certain cases.--(1) Where, after the date of the`
  line `commencement of the Hindu Succession (Tamil Nadu Amendment) Act, 1989, an interest in any`
  line `immovable property of an intestate or in any business carried on by him or her, whether solely or in`
  line `conjunction with others, devolves under section 29-A or section 29-B upon two or more heirs, and`
  line `any one of such heirs proposes to transfer his or her interest in the property or business, the other`
  line `heirs shall have a preferential right to acquire the interest proposed to be transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The consideration for which any interest in the property of the deceased may be transferred`
  line `under this section shall, in the absence of any agreement between the parties, be determined by the`
  line `court on application being made to it in this behalf, and if any person proposing to acquire the interest`
  line `is not willing to acquire it for the consideration so determined, such person shall be liable to pay all`
  line `costs of, or incidental to, the application.`
  line
  line `(3) If there are two or more heirs proposing to acquire any interest under this section, that heir`
  line `who offers the highest consideration for the transfer shall be preferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "court" means the court within the limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `immovable property is situate or the business is carried on and includes any other court which the`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the Tamil Nadu Government Gazette, specify in this`
  line `behalf.".]`
  line
  line `[Vide Tamil Nadu Act 1 of 1990, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (29948)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Testamentary succession`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239&sectionId=29948&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00027_195630_1517807324239
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `*** Any Hindu may dispose of by will or other testamentary`
  line `disposition any property, which is capable of being so ^2[disposed of by him or by her], in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925), or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force and applicable to Hindus.`
  line
  line `Explanation.―The interest of a male Hindu in a Mitakshara coparcenaryproperty or the interest of a`
  line `member of a tarwad, tavazhi, illom, kutumba or kavaru in the property of the tarwad, tavazhi, illom,`
  line `kutumba or kavaru shall, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, be deemed to be property capable of being disposed of by him or by her within the`
  line `meaning of this ^3[section.]`
  line
  line `^4* * ** *`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure (1) omitted by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2005, s. 6, for disposed of by him (w.e.f. 9-9-2005).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule for sub-section (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  line `4. Omitted by Act 78 of 1956, s. 29 (w.e.f. 21-12-1956).`
